description:
Shabby Cane
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Light Arrow
name: Wand of Dregs
note:
<dPlnText:A wand of dead branches, rather unreliable.
Not a catalyst, but rather a blunt weapon.
　
This one has lost the blessing of the stars 
that once shone so brightly indeed.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A sturdy wooden stick.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Rumble
name: Sturdy Stick
note:
<dPlnText:A polished wooden stick.
A simple weapon, but easy to use and powerful.
　
After all, even monsters possess Mana.
Maybe they'll become more docile if you hit them enough.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Tool for splitting firewood.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Fighting Spirit
name: Woodcutting Axe
note:
<dPlnText:Axe for chopping wood.
Not a weapon, but just as deadly.
　
Can easily cut through flesh and bone,
but rather weak against hard shells and metals.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A sword imbued with magical power.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magical Blade
name: Magic Sword
note:
<dPlnText:A weapon imbued with magical power.
Sharpen it, and you have a magical blade.
　
That being said, the sword itself is ordinary,
and has nothing special about it whatsoever.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A weapon that shoots bullets with the power of Mana.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Penetrator
name: Mana Shooter
note:
<dPlnText:Short rifle, popular in certain areas.
It functions by utilizing the holder's Mana.
　
Rather than releasing Mana, it actually
uses Mana to propel bullets forward.
This common misconception is very much frowned upon by experts.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +5%>

description:
A shining blue cane.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosion
name: Azure Wand
note:
<dPlnText:High quality catalyst.
It emits a magical radiance.
　
That blue glow is a tell of its magical prowess.
Should the user's ability be inferior,
it will exert greater power to match it.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +5>

description:
A weapon that is both staff and sword.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magical Blade
name: Ruinous Swordstaff
note:
<dPlnText:Weapon unique to Vilea.
Has the properties of both staff and sword.
　
Perhaps because the Sky Ruins are from
so long ago, such rare objects are now
commonplace even in Ordwald.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +5>

description:
A special cane made by a monster.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Jasmine of Life, Lily of Death
name: Flower Wand
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A gift from the fairies.
Filled with much appreciation.
　
The magical power of the colorful
flower begets life and death.
　
Special Effects:
・SP Cost -10%>

description:
A degraded metal bar.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Rumble
name: Rusty Tool
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A metal bar.
Rusted and deteriorated.
　
It's not a weapon to begin with, and it's not in
good condition either. Absolutely terrible impact.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate -100%>

description:
Handmade fishing rod.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Line and Sinker
name: Fishing Rod
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A fishing rod made from tree branches and vines.
Considering the material, pretty well made.
　
It's just a tool, no lethal force in particular.
The carelessness of using this in a real battle
may well earn the enemy's wrath.
　
Special Effects:
・Chance to be Targeted +1000%>

description:
A mechanical sword with a red-hot blade.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Meltdown
name: Electric Sword
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A really hot sword.
Due to its nature, it can also cut metal.
　
Since heat is amplified by magical power, a talent for
magic is also required to bring out its performance.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Fire attribute.>

description:
A spear wielded by an Ant Knight.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Sharp Thrusts
name: Spear of Jamlav
note:
<NameColor:23>
<BoostEX:CR, 30>
<dPlnText:A spear with a needle-like blade. A weapon
 wielded by the castle knights, who once existed above ground.
　
Once upon a time, a queen ruled over various races
and with her command secured the piece of Tantari.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +20%
・Critical DMG +30%>

description:
A cane that regained its light.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]星龍輝耀
name: Star Dragon
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:From the beginning, this staff is what Ino held.
Blessed by the stars, it has regained its luster.
　
That child was never abandoned.
As a forerunner of hope against the unleashed calamity,
they departed from Asylum in pursuit.
　
Only, that he has given away his memory
in his purpose to becoming human.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Light attribute>

description:
A weapon remembered by someone.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Master Stroke
name: Sword of Tradition
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Equipments spun from memories.
High quality, and easy to handle.
　
Good things are memorable.
Against our excemplary enemy, powerful and memorable,
we must counter them with our own strength.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +8%>

description:
The horns of a mountain-like beast.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Slam
name: Large Mallet
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Loot from battle against a powerful enemy.
Giant Horns of the Great Peak of Auli.
　
Robust and massive, the proof of the king of beasts.
Wield its power and the earth shakes.
　
Special Effects:
・Recover 5% HP every Turn>

description:
Hands that glow in complex colors.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Rainbow Encounter
name: Prism Needle
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Loot from battle against a powerful enemy.
An object so colorful it doesn't seem real.
　
The monster floated in the distant sky,
and came upon something hard to describe.
　
Special Effects:
・Non-Wave DMG taken -10%>

description:
A weapon made from Ino's memory.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Star Dragon Brilliance, Waves of Myth
name: Calamity Star Staff
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:The staff Ino had was transformed.
Darkness creeps up to the light of the stars.
　
Many times over, the world ends and begins anew.
What lies in the scenery between each
is but two figures, a boy and a girl.
　
Special Effects:
・Attack gains the Light and Dark attribute
・Recovers 10% SP every Turn
・Recovers 10 TP every Turn>

description:
Adventurer Luora's Gift
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Heavy Strike - Twin Swords Dance
name: Double Edged Sword
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A pair of swords wielded by the adventurer Luora.
Each are large weapons for one hand in their own right.
　
The blades are marked with numerous scars,
each telling a tale of them and their Lord.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Weapons wielded by monsters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Precise Attack
name: Sharp Claws
note:
<dPlnText:Greatly sharpened claws.
Basically any monster can use this.
　
Heck, even other races can use monster weapons,
but everyone agreed it just didn't feel right.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A dagger wielded by a small barbarian.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Precise Attack
name: Monster Dagger
note:
<dPlnText:A very small dagger.
Its sharpness is also debatable.
　
It's a crude weapon, and it's difficult for humans to handle.
Demonstrates its true value only in the presence of a monster.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A stone that's easy to grasp.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Triple Attack
name: Stone Fist
note:
<dPlnText:A chunk of stone.
Pick it up, and smack with it.
　
Is this really a weapon? Really, it shouldn't
contribute much more than your own power.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A weapon imbued with a monster's prayer.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flying Slash
name: Blade of Prayer
note:
<dPlnText:Highly lethal weapon.
The blade is sharp and contains magic within.
　
The prayers of demons are usually simple.
This weapon, for example, was only blessed to be powerful.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Standard equipment for mechanical dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Precise Attack
name: Machine Doll Sword
note:
<dPlnText:Machine Doll accessories.
Its weight cannot be moved by the human body.
　
It's for mechanical dolls, so it's a violation if
someone who isn't a mechanical doll
gets hold of it.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A magical weapon wielded by monsters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosion
name: Magic Branch
note:
<dPlnText:A small tree branch that holds magical powers.
Basically any monster can use this.
　
Heck, even other races can use monster weapons,
but everyone agreed it just didn't feel right.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Ceremonial tool handed down to barbarians.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosion
name: Magic Stick
note:
<dPlnText:Tools for a certain ritual.
It is said to have been used by shamans,
　
but such monsters no longer exist.
Their cruelty was shunned even by their compatriots.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A magical book that only monsters can read.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Spreading
name: Monster Knowledge
note:
<dPlnText:The first thing a magician pens in their life.
It contains the fundamentals of all magic.
　
Originally, the world referred to a race of monsters,
and now their way of life has become a title
and a guiding principle.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A tool that concentrates magic to the hands.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magical Strike
name: Magic Hand
note:
<dPlnText:Gloves that collect and hold magic within,
and then strike upon the enemy.
　
It might seem convenient for a human, but
monsters who can manifest magical powers can
also just manipulate the magic themselves.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Prototype equipment for mechanical dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosion
name: Machine Doll Wand
note:
<dPlnText:Machine Doll accessories.
Its weight cannot be moved by the human body.
　
It's for mechanical dolls, so it's a violation if
someone who isn't a mechanical doll
gets hold of it.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A book created by a shaman.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Tusk
name: Barbarian Spellbook
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Bloody abomination of a book.
A brutal spell is sealed within.
　
In the early days of Ront, heretical barbarians ruled the mountains.
Numerous sorcery created through gruesome rituals
were later buried by their masters.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +5%>

description:
A fang that fell out from a snake monster.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Toxic Fang
name: Venomous Fang
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Fangs that still ooze poison even after falling out.
Basically any monster can use this.
　
The poison maintains its sharpness,
and murderous intent oozes throughout.
　
It is said that when there were a queen of the
Snake Women, no infighting was seen throughout.
　
Special Effects:
・Negate ATK Down
・Negate Great ATK Down>

description:
An old hunter's weapon.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Ice Arrow
name: Snow Hunting Bow
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Weapons of the clan known as the Snow Hunters.
The monster who wields the weapon is chosen by it.
　
The Snow Hunters confronted the cold abyss enveloping the stars,
but couldn't overcome the everpresent threat of nature.
　
However, the will to live for the sake of their friends
has been passed down upon the present.
　
Special Effects:
・Negate Darkness>

description:
Armament of the Tetra Device.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Beam Module
name: Tetra Bit
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Int'oma's Mechanical Weapon.
Requires special concentration to use.
　
Tetra Devices are guardians of the Sky Ruins.
Now that it fell down, everything seems
to it like an intruder indeed.
　
Special Effects:
・Remove 5 TP every Turn>

description:
Shears belonging to a crab monster.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Bubble
name: Crab Shears
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Crab shears in good condition.
Freshly obtained without a single blemish.
　
Feels more like a blunt weapon.
And also a little like armor.
　
Blows bubbles despite not being a mouth.
　
Special Effects:
・Negate Stun>

description:
Bluntly, a very thorny weapon.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Bone Splitter
name: Rebuke of Grace
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A sinister weapon.
Needless to say, this WILL hurt.
　
It appears it has been wielded on numerous occasions.
The spines are stained with blood
　
We fear them because we did not believe,
that those very wounds are caused by love.
　
Special Effects:
・TP Gain Rate +50%>

description:
A type of weapon for Machine Dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]-
name: Missile Shooter
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Special armament for Machine Dolls.
Launches small missiles.
　
There are no set rules for arming mechanical dolls,
and each was invented independently.
Therefore, such ambitious works are rare.
　
Special Effects:
・On Normal Attack, AGI +200>

description:
A certain Nightmare's self-defense weapon.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Yotogi's Secret
name: Yotogi's Dagger
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A Shikinoa-style dagger.
Features a glossy decorative scabbard.
　
In the East, Nightmares are called Yotogi,
and they are also treated rather differently.
　
Special Effects:
・Recover 4 TP every Turn>

description:
A weapon once used by a maiden of stagnation.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Rite of Stagnation
name: Shrine Maiden's Ceremony
note:
<BoostEX:MG, 10>
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Ordwald's treasure.
Consists of a blade shaped by magic.
　
Once, a shrine maiden casted the Rite in the sea of darkness
to rest the pulse of stagnation.
　
Special Effects:
・Magic attacks +10% power>

description:
A weapon remembered by someone.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Master Stroke
name: Legendary Blade
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Equipments spun from memories.
High quality, and easy to handle.
　
Good things are memorable.
Against our excemplary enemy, powerful and memorable,
we must counter them with our own strength.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +8%>

description:
One of the Machine Dolls' armaments.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Burst Shot
name: Beam Rifle
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Loot from battle against a powerful enemy.
Entangled in the roots of a mutated thundertree.
　
The weapon's form looks unfit to Certilt's.
Someone must have dropped it on the way.
　
Special Effects:
・AGI +100 on Normal Attack>

description:
Fiery hair of a Nightmare, bends like a whip.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magic Return
name: Kanlua Hair
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Loot from battle against a powerful enemy.
The source of the power of the bear dragonfish.
　
It seems to have once hosted a great flame,
but it has since faded, leaving only magic.
　
Special Effects:
・MAG +5%>

description:
Ritual equipment used in witchcraft.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Crimson Flame
name: Barbarian Wand
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Loot from battle against a powerful enemy.
The very cursed ritual itself.
　
After some time, rituals are governed by implements,
and sorcerers only follow them as pawns.
　
Special Effects:
・Negate Confusion>

description:
Weapons of Twin Machine Dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Spiral Inject
name: Drill Unit
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Loot from battle against a powerful enemy.
Weapons given to mechanical twins.
　
An excavating machine,
once used to expand the ruins.
That was once the twins' mission.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical Rate +10%>

description:
A weapon wielded by the hunters of Tarvilal.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Concentration, Binding Tool
name: Multi-Binder
note:
<NameColor:2>
<BoostEX:CR, 30>
<dPlnText:Hunter's restraint weapons.
Handled by those with superior skill.
　
A hunter's weapon shall be hidden to the self.
To give it to others is the proof that
you have absolute trust in them.
　
Special Effects:
・Critical DMG +30%>

description:
A weapon forged from the memories of Kanlua.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flaming Climax
name: Twisted Uneven Horns
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the Lord of Reason's legacy.
You can wield but a glimpse of that power.
　
The Nightmare's horns are irregular and
distorted from the influence of its own magic,
becoming a symbol of her power.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Fire attribute
・Recover 10 TP every Turn
・Negate Poison>

description:
A weapon forged from the memories of Valco.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Thunderstrike
name: Thunder Curse Sacrifice
note:
<NameColor:2>
<反撃拡張:雷呪の贄>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the Lord of Reason's legacy.
You can wield but a glimpse of that power.
　
The villagers offered sacrifices
and prayed to the tree, fearing the curse of falling thunder,
not knowing that it was the curse itself.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Thunder attribute
・Activates [Thundershock] on Physical DMG taken
・Negate Forgetful>

description:
A weapon forged from the memories of Muracca.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Ice Impact
name: Ice Claw of the Mad Hunt
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the Lord of Reason's legacy.
You can wield but a glimpse of that power.
　
A hunter kills prey to survive.
But she doesn't hunt just to stay alive,
and therefore she succumbs to madness.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Ice Attribute.
・Critical Rate and Evasion Rate +10%
・Negate Confusion>

description:
A weapon forged from the memories of Kilma.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Sword of Regression
name: Sword of Stagnation
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the Lord of Reason's legacy.
You can wield but a glimpse of that power.
　
Sin sinks to the bottom, and the water stagnates.
During the ceremony, those shrine maidens
lost their mission to thoughtlessness.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Water attribute
・Physical and Magical DMG taken -10%
・Negate Fatigue>

description:
A weapon forged from the memories of Luora.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Crystal Polish
name: Sword of Slaughter
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the Lord of Reason's legacy.
You can wield but a glimpse of that power.
　
A pair of swords with numerous scars.
It is not proof of the ability to cut down everyone before it,
but the will to protect everyone behind it.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Earth attribute
・ATK +10%
・Negate Paralysis>

description:
A weapon crafted from Tyvar's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Storm Embrace
name: Maelstorm of Karmic Ode
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the Lord of Reason's legacy.
You can wield but a glimpse of that power.
　
Ancient dragons gather in the continent of Seifu,
waiting for an old friend in a rusty shrine.
　
Special Effects:
・Attacks gain the Wind attribute
・Recover 10% HP every Turn
・Negate Stun>
